# mmseqs easy-search is already IUPAC aware, i think. 
# minimap2 is not, but the forked version used here is. 

# Probably a more systematic benchmark is necissary. 
# A limitation: PrinTE/bin/shared_ltr_inserter_parallel creates fragmented LTR-RTs by chopping between 50% and 90% from one end. THis will create some solo-LTR lookalikes if fragmentation happens to chop near the LTR. They wont have TSDs though. Maybe its a minimal issue not worth adjusting. 

# Im not exactly happy with the minimap2 parameters. A more systmentic parameter sweep of those may be helpful in recovering additional F1 gain. 
# Currently, using TSD appears to be give the best result, although this sucks, since its based on LTR-RT boundary detection, so error at the LTR-RT detection step leads to error at solo-LTR step. These are compounding errors where solo-LTR detection can only be as strong as the boundary determination during LTR-RT detection. 
# A better benchmark would decouple LTR-RT detection from solo-LTR bencmarking. ie, assume LTR-RT detection was perfect and boundaries were perfect. Just LTR-RTs and LTRs without detection de novo and use this theorretical perfect annotion to benchmark solo-LTR parameters. This will give better granularity of the strengths of this apprach specifically without seeing the compounded error in my metrocs. 

 
